We set

$$\begin{aligned}
\smooth_0^\infty([a,b],\R^n) &\coloneqq
  \left\{\,
    Y \in \smooth^\infty([a,b],\R^n) \Bigm| \exists\delta > 0\colon
    Y\bigr|_{[a,a+\delta] \cup [b-\delta,b]} \equiv 0\,
  \right\}, \\
\smooth_0^\infty[a,b] &\coloneqq \smooth_0^\infty([a,b],\R).
\end{aligned}$$

In particular, all variational vector fields of variations of plane curves with compact support are contained in $$\smooth_0^\infty([a,b],\R^2).$$

''Lemma.''
For all vector fields
$$Y \in \smooth_0^\infty([0,L],\R^2)$$
and every parametrized curve there is a variation $$\gamma$$ such that $$\dot\gamma = Y.$$

